popup_text = "[b][color=#093C5D]Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)[/color][/b]
OOP[color=#3B7597] organizes [/color]programs using objects and classes.

[b][color=#093C5D]Class[/color][/b]
Blueprint for creating objects.

[b][color=#093C5D]Object[/color][/b]
Instance of a class.

Example:
Class: Car
Object: Toyota

[b][color=#093C5D]Inheritance[/color][/b]
Inheritance allows one class to acquire properties and methods from another class.

Purpose:
Reuse code
Create relationships between classes

Example:
Animal → Parent class
Dog → Child class

[b][color=#093C5D]Encapsulation[/color][/b]
Encapsulation hides data and controls access using methods.

Usually done using:
private variables
getter and setter methods

[b][color=#093C5D]Polymorphism[/color][/b]
Polymorphism allows one method to behave differently in different classes.
"
